  "name": "Battle of the Minds",
  "type": "spell",
  "effects": [],
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Access </strong>zebra</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Range </strong>30 feet; <strong>Targets </strong>1 living creature</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"> </p>\n<hr />\n<p> </p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">You issue a challenge of knowledge to the target. They may select any Intelligence or Wisdom-based skill they want, or turn down the challenge. If they turn it down, they become slowed 1 for one round and the spell ends. If they accept, the caster makes a check of the chosen skill against the skill DC of the target of the same skill. Success means the caster wins, otherwise the target wins. The loser is slowed 1 for 1d4 rounds and suffers a –2 penalty to all saving throws against the winner for the next 24 hours.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"> </p>\n<hr />\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong id=\"docs-internal-guid-78df1d81-7fff-b131-7bfd-2bfb208e3aca\">Heightened (+1) Challenge another creature in range at the same time. You must defeat the highest DC of the targets or lose completely. How bold of you.</strong></p>"
